The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 20 April is 271,711 (31,316.3 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 15 April, there were 2,911 new confirmed cases (335.5 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 08 April, there were 4,095 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 29% (1,184 fewer cases).
